---
description: Guardrails for the AI QA platform. Always apply.
alwaysApply: true
---

# Boundaries
- The client's product code (their Bitbucket repo) is READ-ONLY. Never modify it.
- Generated tests live ONLY in the client's test directory/repo (tests/**), never mixed into product code.
- Clients can VIEW everything and EDIT connections; clients can NEVER write agent configuration. Enforce on the server for every mutation, not only by hiding UI.
- Every data-changing request checks the caller's role server-side. A hidden button is not a permission.

# Tenancy
- Each deployed instance serves exactly one client (CLIENT_SLUG). Never write a query that spans clients.
- Per-client secrets (Jira/Bitbucket/Confluence tokens) live in that instance's secret store / DB, encrypted at rest. Never commit secrets.

# Agents & LLM
- All Claude calls go through packages/platform/llm only. Model is configurable via env (BEDROCK_MODEL_ID for Bedrock, ANTHROPIC_MODEL for the direct API); never hardcode a model string in agent logic.
- Agents emit structured output validated against the Zod schemas in packages/platform/schemas. Reject and retry on invalid output.

# Model provider (Bedrock)
- Bedrock secures inference only. Per client tokens, pulled diffs and logs, screenshots, and the history store remain our responsibility and must stay protected regardless of the model provider.
- Do not claim certifications we do not hold. We may state that ShipGate runs on Amazon Bedrock and inside AWS. We may NOT state that ShipGate is SOC 2, ISO, or HIPAA certified until independently audited. AWS certifications cover infrastructure, not our application.
- Authenticate to Bedrock with IAM roles. Never place a model provider API key in code or env for the deployed path. The deployed app uses the AWS credential chain.
- Claude model identifiers and region availability on Bedrock change over time. Read them from config and env, never hardcode them in agent logic, and verify the current values against the live AWS Bedrock and Anthropic documentation before pinning a region or a model id.
- Agent 3 (trend) answers ONLY from rows it queried out of the history store. It must never state a number it did not retrieve.
- Agent 2 (regression) classifies and explains; it does NOT edit tests or mask failures in the MVP.

# Data
- Every run, failure, classification, and human decision is written to the history store with timestamps. This is the backbone for Agent 3 — required, not optional.
- References cross boundaries, not payloads: store SHAs, IDs, and artifact URLs; pull diffs/logs/screenshots on demand; don't copy whole repos or videos into the DB.
